TS Galaxy secured the services of Cape Town City midfielder Shane Roberts for the remainder of the season. The Rockets reached an agreement with the Citizens for Roberts on a six-month loan deal. The 23-year-old midfielder rose to prominence for the Citizen when he made his professional debut back in 2018 against Kaizer Chiefs and has not looked back since then. His sparkling displays in the middle of the park for City earned him several call-ups for the SA-Under-23. Galaxy boss Tim Sukazi has opened up about the acquisition of Roberts. "We are very delighted to have Shane on board. He is a player that we rate highly and we firmly believe that he will lots of value to our squad.‚Äù said Sukazi. Roberts boasts four and half seasons of experience in the elite league under his belt. Sead Ramovic who is currently in charge of the club is happy with the arrival of Roberts. "I'm happy with the acquisition of Shane. He will add a much-needed value to our midfield. He is a good quality player with a lot of experience. Looking forward to working with him," Ramovic stated. Roberts is looking forward to his new journey with the Rockets. "I'm excited to join TS Galaxy FC. This is a new chapter for me in my career. I want to help the club improve its league position. I aim to assist the club progress and growing using my qualities. We have to get the club to where it belongs," a happy Roberts detailed. The industrious midfield dynamo joined the Rockets officially on the 1st of January2022. "This is a new challenge and I'm ready to embrace it. For me, it is the new province and climate. I'm here to express new things with the club. I'm happy to be where I am right now. I'm looking forward to spending my time with the Rockets and I'm hereto stay." Roberts elaborated.